blog.name: i-blame-the-bbc
blog.title: Day Of Eternity
blog.description:
This Girl is made of mud and clay, with ambers for eyes.

She sups with the ghosts of wolves

and sleeps with dragons made of lilac petals.

The blackbirds are Her family.

She knows all that the trees do.

This Girl wears Her grandfather’s wheat on Her head,

and Her eyes see stormy waves crashing against grey stone cliffs.

She was born in the crater left by a blitz bomb that never lived.

When Her anchor died, She left for the stars,

where She communicates using rainbows, and is now empress of Saturn.

This Girl has eyes centuries old, yet has not seen a decade.

She has skin of paper, with charcoal for eyes and used firewood for hair.

She works with fabrics made of light and numbers

and can see evil like a blanket.

She is brave but was scared of the sounds the sky made,

so She ran to the stars.

She saved the earth and killed the dinosaurs,

but still has nightmares of the things that killed Her.

This girl used to be buttermilk, bruised and burnt, with blood for hair.

She was prey, whose only escape was knowledge.

Until the day when she decided to take power from the burns.

To become the fire.

Now, this Girl is equal part phoenix and fox.

When happy, Her eyes contain a hearth fire kindling on Christmas day.

When upset, Her eyes show a forest fire, hungry for something to

burn.

Her hair is now wine that sets aflame in the dark and cold.

With footsteps of of shadow, fire as Her armour,

and knowledge as Her weapon,

She is now a hunter.

This Girl is a golden flower, caught in a beam of summer sunlight

Her father is a straying star. Her mother is the void.

She is a dragon with a crown.

Queen of both the people with platinum mines for heads

and vineyards for hands,

and the people who sing golden oceans

and have shelters for hearts.

She dances on snow and can see across the world to its edge.

With her twin Silver Gifts and her trusty hart,

she is a Golden Darkness.

These Girls are Beautiful.

These Girls are from the wild.

And like many beautiful things in the wild,

they are also very deadly.

Marvel Confirms Thanos Brings People Back Using Infinity Stones in Avengers: Endgame

In one of the latest trailer for Marvel Studios’ Avengers: Endgame, a line of dialogue from Captain Marvel indicates that Thanos has brought a number of people back after snapping them out of existence.
